<h2>What Is On-Page SEO?</h2>

<p>
On-page SEO is the process of optimizing elements on your website to improve rankings.
</p>

<p>
This includes:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Content optimization</li>
<li>Keyword placement</li>
<li>Internal linking</li>
<li>Meta tags</li>
</ul>

<p>
Businesses use  
<a href="#services" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">
on-page SEO services in Kenya
</a>  
to improve visibility and traffic.
</p>

---

<h2>1. Keyword Optimization (The Foundation)</h2>

<p>
Every page should target a primary keyword.
</p>

<p>
Example:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Primary: “on-page SEO checklist”</li>
<li>Secondary: “SEO optimization tips for beginners”</li>
<li>Long-tail: “how to optimize website pages for SEO in Kenya”</li>
</ul>

<p>
👉 Place keywords in:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Title</li>
<li>Headings</li>
<li>First paragraph</li>
<li>Meta description</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>2. Title Tag Optimization</h2>

<p>
Your title must:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Include your keyword</li>
<li>Be clear and clickable</li>
<li>Stay under 60 characters</li>
</ul>

<p>
Example:
<strong>“On-Page SEO Checklist for Beginners (2026 Guide)”</strong>
</p>

---

<h2>3. Meta Description Optimization</h2>

<p>
Meta descriptions increase clicks.
</p>

<p>
Best practices:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Include keywords</li>
<li>Make it compelling</li>
<li>Keep under 160 characters</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>4. Header Tags (H1, H2, H3)</h2>

<p>
Use headings to structure your content.
</p>

<ul>
<li>H1: Main title</li>
<li>H2: Sections</li>
<li>H3: Subsections</li>
</ul>

<p>
This improves readability and SEO.
</p>

---

<h2>5. Content Quality & Search Intent</h2>

<p>
Google ranks content that matches user intent.
</p>

<p>
Your content must:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Answer questions clearly</li>
<li>Provide value</li>
<li>Be easy to read</li>
</ul>

<p>
If your content isn’t ranking, read:  
